      "description": "This 2010 Porsche Cayman S features the sought-after 3.4L DFI flat-six engine, delivering linear power and a visceral 7,500 RPM redline. The mid-engine architecture offers a low polar moment of inertia, resulting in exceptional chassis balance and neutral handling through high-G corners. This example is equipped with a crisp 6-speed manual gearbox and a mechanical limited-slip differential for optimal torque vectoring. The suspension remains taut, with the MacPherson strut arrangement providing communicative feedback through the hydraulic steering rack. Recent maintenance includes a comprehensive borescope inspection and fluid analysis, confirming the integrity of the MA1.21 powertrain. A mechanically sound, driver-focused specimen ready for the apex.",
